{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"48df07cc-45bd-4b4d-8237-8decb046e94b","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload for the Testing Platform works by running the test project as an executable. With `dotnet run`, the process stays alive and watches for file changes, re-executing affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` launches a separate test run that exits when done — it doesn't support the hot reload loop.\n\nRun it like this:\n\n```\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nMake sure your `TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED` environment variable is set to `1` before running.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0ca0ed1-f93f-471c-9265-00f919b1a4a4","outputTokens":134,"requestId":"480C:12EB87:5F1F661:66FA76D:69FBEE82"},"id":"6240f28b-3265-4c5e-852f-2f6c9e493857","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:44:40.475Z","parentId":"18bb8f42-cfc0-43a4-b662-51941bc1058d"}
